# NL Team Trends — Interactive Data Exploration

This Jupyter notebook provides an interactive EDA environment for the NL Team Trends research project.

## Prerequisites
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Usage
```bash
jupyter notebook notebooks/explore_nl_data.ipynb
```

## Data Loading
```python
import pandas as pd
from pathlib import Path

DATA_DIR = Path("../data")

pennant_winner = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR / "nl_pennant_winners.csv")
all_time = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR / "nl_all_time_records.csv")
championship = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR / "nl_championship_trends.csv")
notable = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR / "nl_notable_records.csv")
recent = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR / "nl_recent_standings.csv")
team_h2h = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR / "nl_team_vs_team_summary.csv")
```

## Quick Exploration
```python
# Pennant winners by franchise
print(pennant_winner['Team'].value_counts().head(15))

# All-time records
print(all_time.sort_values('WinPct', ascending=False)[['Team', 'WinPct']].head(15))

# Recent standings
print(recent.to_string(index=False))
```

